<div1><?Pub Dtl?>
	<head>Link Recognition</head>
	<p>The existsnce of a <termref def="dt-link">link</termref> is asserted by a <termref def="dt-linkel">linking element</termref>. Linking elements must be recognized reliably by application nk. It then follows the behavior set out in the <code>show</code> option.</p>
		<!-- Something should be put here in terms of an example. Idea: "A" link versus automatically updating encyclopedia. -bent -->
	</div2>

	<div2 id="link-semantics">
		<head>Sem<termdef id="dt-arc" term="Arc">An <term>arc</term> is contained within an extended link for the purpose of defining traversal behavior.</termdef> More than one arc may be associated with a link. Otherwise, arc elements function exactly as the arc attributes mi></p>
<p>Note that conformance is assessed at the level of individualn whole XML documents, because XLink and non-XLink linking mechanisms
may be used side by side in any one document.</p>
